Currently the function membersOf("") only can search members of a group. We require to search for members of a project role. Can this be added to the functionality of this function? This could be implemented sending 2 parameters to the function:

membersOf("project_role_name", "role") or membersOf("group_name", "group")

The query that we use to generate Due issues is like this:
{code}
http://localhost:8080/jira/secure/IssueNavigator.jspa?reset=true&jqlQuery=project+%3D+HSP+AND+resolution+%3D+Unresolved+ORDER+BY+due+ASC%2C+priority+DESC%2C+created+ASC&mode=hide
{code}

It would make sense to add 'AND due is not empty' to the query so that we do not include issues that have no due date set on them.

See this comment: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Subtask+creation+form+enhancements?focusedCommentId=207487617#comment-207487617



